<topic id = "id131JK0R0VPN"
    xmlns:ditaarch = "http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/">
<title>Flatten Cross-ref Formats</title>
<shortdesc>Sets the value of all cross-ref formats to null (an empty
string) in the current file or book.</shortdesc>
<prolog><author>Scott Prentice</author>
<critdates><created date = "2013-01-19"/>
<revised modified = "2013-08-04"/></critdates></prolog>
<body><p><indexterm>cross-ref<indexterm>formats</indexterm></indexterm>Running
this command prevents the save to XML from pushing the content of
a cross-ref outside of the xref element. This is not needed if you
use the Fix/Flatten Cross-Refs command, but if youâ€™re not using
that, you should probably run this command instead.</p>
<p>Note that after running this command, all resolved cross-refs
will be empty (and appear to be missing), but they will convert
to empty xref elements after applying the conversion table.</p>
<p>Run this command before applying a conversion table.</p></body></topic>
